Part A: Angle Review

Identify each angle (acute/obtuse/right/straight):
a. 12°
b. 98°
c. 180°
d. 75°

Draw a right angle and label it ∠XYZ.

Part B: Classify & Compare Shapes

Which shapes have exactly one line of symmetry?
a. Square
b. Rectangle (not a square)
c. Scalene triangle
d. Isosceles triangle

List two ways a square and a rhombus are the same, and one way they are different.

Part C: Area, Perimeter & Volume

A rectangle has an area of 48 square meters and a width of 6 meters.
What is its length?

A garden is shaped like a square with a side length of 11 feet.
What is the perimeter?

Find the volume: l = 9 cm, w = 4 cm, h = 3 cm.

Part D: Coordinate Plane

Plot the following points on a coordinate grid (teacher provides grid):

A(2, 5)

B(2, 1)

C(7, 1)

D(7, 5)

Then answer:

What shape do points A, B, C, and D form?

What is the perimeter of this shape?

What is the area?

Part E: Word Problems

A picture frame is 14 inches long and 8 inches wide.
What is its perimeter?

A rectangular prism has volume 240 cubic cm.
If the base is 10 cm × 4 cm, what is the height?

A triangle has angle measures 35° and 75°.
What is the third angle?